Describe a rule you dislike and would like to change in the future
- what it is
- what it is for
- why you don't like it
- explain why you would like to change it

I’d like to talk about a rule that I really dislike, which is the strict dress code in some schools and workplaces.

Basically, in many places, students or employees are required to wear uniforms or formal clothes every day. The idea behind this rule is to promote discipline, professionalism, and a sense of equality, but personally, I find it quite restrictive.

I remember when I was in high school, we had to wear the same uniform every day, even during really hot weather. It was quite uncomfortable, especially in the summer, and sometimes I felt it affected my mood and concentration.

One reason I don’t like this rule is that it limits self-expression. I think clothing is a way people show their personality, so being forced to dress in a certain way can feel a bit frustrating. Another issue is practicality—formal clothes or uniforms aren’t always suitable for different weather conditions, and they can also be quite expensive for some families.

I think this rule should be more flexible. For example, schools and workplaces could allow a smart-casual dress code instead. This way, people can still look presentable while feeling more comfortable.

Overall, I believe a more relaxed dress code would create a better atmosphere and help people feel more confident and productive.
